steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2ts99","text":"Prepare the three separate solutions needed for this extraction protocol as listed below.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2er0m","text":" lipid extraction solvent (step 2) with a 1:1 ratio of butanol and lab purified water (water-saturated butanol, and lab purified water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8g7vv","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"reagents","mutability":"","data":{"id":4571,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Butanol","linfor":"","url":"","sku":"71-36-3","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":1,"can_edit":0,"guid":"00705CACAC394F338027EBAF0C485CFD","in_steps":null,"vendor":{"id":159,"name":"Fischer Scientific","link":"https://www.fishersci.com/","image":{"source":"/img/vendors/placeholder.png","placeholder":"/img/vendors/placeholder.png"}}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c0s9u","text":"Prepare the three separate solutions needed for this extraction protocol as follows:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"54p6k","text":"lipid extraction solvent: a 15 : 15 : 5 : 1 : 0.18 ratio by volume of 95% ethanol, water, diethyl ether, pyridine, and 4.2 N ammonium hydroxide, respectively.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"be5nh","text":"water-saturated butanol:  a 1:1 ratio of butanol and Milli-Q water","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a2g4e","text":"purified lab water: (Milli-Q water) ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"at5qq","text":"Unfold polycarbonate filter and place into a 2-mL centrifuge tube with cell side of filter facing outwards.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"264sq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4b1jj","text":"Note: Appropriate volume of lab culture or field samples to filter and extract depends on cell concentration.  As a guideline, we have been successful filtering 10-25 mL of lab cultures of Microcystis aeruginosa and ~50 mL of either raw lake water or mesocosm samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":189,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ar6sb","text":"Add 1 mL of extraction solvent, ~100 µL of glass beads, and vortex ~5 s. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dmqdb","text":"Remove supernatant and place into a 1-dram glass vial (dram vial #1).  The first two extractions from a sample will be placed in this vial (#1).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7kb41","text":"Repeat steps 3-6, except DO NOT ADD more glass beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"j4u4","text":"Dry the collected supernatant in dram vial #1 under a stream of nitrogen.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6k1la","text":"Re-suspend dried sample in 300 µL of water-saturated butanol and 150 µL of Milli-Q water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"23nsf","text":"Remove top butanol phase and place into a NEW 1-dram glass vial (dram vial #2).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"22smt","text":"Wash original dram vial (#1) with 300 µL saturated butanol and transfer to residual aqueous phase in 2-mL centrifuge tube from step 10.  Vortex.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3fck","text":"Centrifuge at 10,000 x g for 2 min.  Remove top butanol phase and place into dram vial #2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6k6u6","text":"Dry the collected butanol phase in dram vial #2 under a stream of nitrogen.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b4ags","text":"The samples are now ready for analysis via LC/MS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":39,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
